President Barack Obama will award Clinton Romesha, a former Army Staff Sergeant, with the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions during combat operations in Afghanistan on October 3, 2009. Romesha will be the fourth living recipient of the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He and his family will be honored at the White House for his selfless service. Romesha enlisted in the Army in 1999 and served in Kosovo, Iraq, and Korea before his deployment to Afghanistan. His military decorations include various campaign medals, commendation medals, and the Combat Action Badge. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate exceptional bravery or self-sacrifice in the face of great danger.